FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778688714
OL,3,CWhat quirky traditions will be on show
OL,4,Cfor the King's speech?
OL,6,FThe State Opening of Parliament marks
OL,7,Fthe start of the new parliamentary
OL,8,Fyear and the government's priorities.
OL,10,FNot only does it represent an
OL,11,Fadministrative date on the calendar
OL,12,Ffor laying out Parliament's agenda,
OL,13,Fbut it also symbolises the primacy of
OL,14,Fthe Commons in the UK constitution.
OL,16,FThe speech represents the symbolic
OL,17,Frole of the King in the constitution,
OL,18,Fand how his power is run through the
OL,19,FCommons, but is written by the
OL,20,Fgovernment of the day.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778688714
OL,3,CWhat quirky traditions will be on show
OL,4,Cfor the King's speech?
OL,6,FThe speech is written entirely by the
OL,7,Fgovernment, but most people are often
OL,8,Fmore interested in the pomp and
OL,9,Fceremony that surrounds it rather than
OL,10,Fwhat the King actually has to say.
OL,12,FWhat is the King's speech?
OL,14,FThe King's Speech is delivered as part
OL,15,Fof the State Opening of Parliament,
OL,16,Fmarking the start of the new
OL,17,Fparliamentary year and the
OL,18,Fgovernment's priorities.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778688714
OL,3,CWhat quirky traditions will be on show
OL,4,Cfor the King's speech?
OL,6,FThe government writes the speech read
OL,7,Fout by the monarch, which is
OL,8,Fconventionally delivered in a neutral
OL,9,Ftone to keep the monarch politically
OL,10,Fimpartial.
OL,12,FAfter the speech, MPs will debate the
OL,13,Flegislative agenda and vote it through
OL,14,FParliament.
OL,16,FThis is the third time King Charles
OL,17,Fhas delivered the parliamentary speech
OL,18,Fas monarch, but he also delivered one
OL,19,Fon behalf of Queen Elizabeth II when
OL,20,Fshe was unwell in May 2022.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778688714
OL,3,CWhat quirky traditions will be on show
OL,4,Cfor the King's speech?
OL,6,FWill the King's speech even go ahead?
OL,8,FDespite the intense speculation around
OL,9,FStarmer's future and the crisis at the
OL,10,Ftop of government, ministers have
OL,11,Fconfirmed the speech will go ahead.
OL,13,FEven if the government collapsed, it
OL,14,Fwould still need to go ahead, as it is
OL,15,Fa requirement for the new
OL,16,FParliamentary session to go ahead.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
