PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778688714
OL,3,CWhat quirky traditions will be on show
OL,4,Cfor the King's speech?
OL,6,FSpeeches by the monarch have been
OL,7,Fsuspended before and the parliamentary
OL,8,Fsession extended, but it has never
OL,9,Fbeen changed so close to the planned
OL,10,Fdate.
OL,12,FStarmer's previous King's Speech was
OL,13,Falso not without its controversy: in
OL,14,FJuly last year, seven Labour MPs from
OL,15,Fthe left of the party were suspended
OL,16,Fwhen they supported an SNP motion to
OL,17,Fabolish the welfare limit rather than
OL,18,Fbacking the bill as it was.
OL,20,FWhat will the day look like?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778688714
OL,3,CWhat quirky traditions will be on show
OL,4,Cfor the King's speech?
OL,6,FThe King will travel to Parliament
OL,7,Ffrom Buckingham Palace by carriage,
OL,8,Farriving through an entrance specially
OL,9,Freserved for the monarch.
OL,11,FHe will then put on the crown and the
OL,12,Frobes of the state, before leading a
OL,13,Fprocession to the throne in the House
OL,14,Fof Lords.
OL,16,FA parliamentary official called Black
OL,17,FRod summons MPs from the Commons to
OL,18,Fthe Lords to watch the speech, which
OL,19,Fusually takes place in the late
OL,20,Fmorning and lasts just over 10 minutes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1778688714
OL,3,CWhat quirky traditions will be on show
OL,4,Cfor the King's speech?
OL,6,FAfter the speech, MPs return to the
OL,7,FCommons, where they begin debating its
OL,8,Fcontents, which lasts for several days
OL,9,Fand features a full response from the
OL,10,Fleader of the opposition, Kemi
OL,11,FBadenoch.
OL,13,FWhy is the day so full of ceremony and
OL,14,Fodd traditions?
OL,16,FThe state opening of Parliament is a
OL,17,Ftradition steeped in history dating
OL,18,Fback to the 16th century, although
OL,19,Fsimilar ceremonies can be traced back
OL,20,Feven further.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
